        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 19 at 7:32PM EDT by NWS Detroit/Pontiac MI</headline>
        <description>At 730 PM EDT, Doppler radar indicated a cluster of strong
thunderstorms along a line extending from Rochester to near
Clarkston to near Oak Grove. Movement was southeast at 25 mph.

HAZARD...Winds in excess of 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs. Minor damage to
outdoor objects is possible.

Strong thunderstorms will be near...
Troy, Pontiac, Hartland, Sterling Heights, and Rochester around
735 PM EDT.
Milford around 740 PM EDT.
Birmingham, Clinton, and West Bloomfield around 745 PM EDT.
Warren and Royal Oak around 750 PM EDT.
Southfield, Novi, and Brighton around 755 PM EDT.
St. Clair Shores and Detroit Zoo around 805 PM EDT.
South Lyon around 810 PM EDT.
Livonia and Northville around 815 PM EDT.

Other locations impacted by these storms include Franklin, Keego
Harbor, Waterford, Shelby Township, Commerce, Utica, Auburn Hills,
Lake Angelus, Harper Woods, and Pleasant Ridge.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
